hese marginal workers, the sum of the law is less than its parts, and, despite what appears to be a plethora of applicable statutes, marginal workers are frequently lacking in protection. To ameliorate the status of marginal workers, he argues for a new paradigm in worker protection, one based on human freedom and rights.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aDiscrimination in employmentxLaw and legislationzUnited States. 0aForeign workersxLegal status, laws, etczUnited States. 0aForeign workersxLegal status, laws, etc.zUnited States. 0aLabor laws and legislationzUnited States. 0aLabor unionsxLaw and legislationzUnited States. 0aMinoritiesxLegal status, laws, etczUnited States. 0aMinoritiesxLegal status, laws, etc.zUnited States. 7aLAW / Emigration & Immigration.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNew York University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z97831107064440 cprintz978081473221240uhttps://doi.org/10.18574/nyu/9780814738627.001.000140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780814738627423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780814738627/original  a978-3-11-070644-4  New York University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LAEC  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LAEC  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles